            . I am a green-grocer, and live in <placeName id="t18190707-36-crimeloc200">Threadneedle-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-36-crimeloc200" type="placeName" value="Threadneedle-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-36-crimeloc200" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-36-off198 t18190707-36-crimeloc200"></join>. On the 6th of July, I saw the prisoner go by my window - I went to the door, suspecting him; he was out of my sight in half a minute. I saw him come out of a house or court with a basket. He crossed the street to Copthall-court. I ran out, overtook him, and asked him what he had got? he said he did not know. I took him back to the court he came out of - the basket had carpenters tools in it; he had taken it from a building in New-court. I sent for an officer, and gave him in charge. He had no basket when he passed my house.</p>
               <p>HERCULES WRIGHT. I am a <rs id="t18190707-36-viclabel201" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-36-victim363 t18190707-36-viclabel201"></join>. I was at work by the Stock Exchange. Some of the tools are mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190707-36-person366">
                  JOHN 
                  HILL
               <interp inst="t18190707-36-person366" type="surname" value="HILL"></interp>
